  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Water Supply and Sanitation Sector, Phase III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the programme is to contribute to poverty reduction through improved access to safe drinking water and hygienic sanitation. The programme has got two components which support policy development at the Ministry of Local Government Division and the implementation of water supply and sanitation activities at the local level. The water supply and sanitation activities are implemented in close collaboration with Union Parishads, the lowest level of local government system in Bangladesh. The major part of the budget in allocated to improvements in water supply and access to hygienic sanitation in rural areas in the north and south of the country and in the Chittagong Hill Tracts. The policy development component is anchored in the Ministry of Local Government Division. The hygiene, water supply and sanitation activites are implemented by the HYSAWA Fund. The programme activities are on track, and expected result have been delivered on time.</narrative>
  </description>
